==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Primrose League
<hw>Prim"rose` League</hw>. <fld>(Eng. Politics)</fld> <def>A league of
both sexes among the Conservatives, founded in 1883. So called because
<xex>primrose</xex> was (erroneously, it is said) taken to be the
favorite flower of the Conservative statesman <person>Benjamin
Disraeli</person>, Earl of Beaconsfield.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Primula</ent>⟦br⟧
